            <title>[SOLR-642] ShardResponse IllegalAccessError</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-642</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As ShardResponse is package protected, any class that makes extention &lt;br/&gt;
of a search component has access issues due to different classloaders.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;java.lang.IllegalAccessError: tried to access class&lt;br/&gt;
org.apache.solr.handler.component.ShardResponse from class&lt;br/&gt;
org.apache.solr.handler.component.MyComponent&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The proposed solution (see Yonik answer on solr-dev) :&lt;br/&gt;
 1. A public scope for the ShardResponse (a class of it&apos;s own)&lt;br/&gt;
 2. Switch public members to private and use getters for the search components&lt;/p&gt;</description>
